  "prompt": "I am a third year mu engineering student. I have one kt in semester 2 will I get grace?",
  "response": "Congratulations on progressing to your third year in engineering! Regarding your situation with having one KT (Keep Term) in Semester 2, whether you receive grace marks or not depends largely on your university's specific policies. Here's a general overview to help you understand the possibilities:\n\n### **Understanding KT (Keep Term)**\n- **KT Defined:** A \"KT\" typically means you have a backlog or need to appear for a supplementary exam for a particular subject or paper.\n- **Implications:** Having a KT doesn't necessarily halt your academic progress, but it indicates that you need to clear that subject to meet graduation requirements.\n\n### **Grace Marks Explained**\n- **Purpose:** Grace marks are additional points awarded to help students meet the passing criteria without reappearing for exams.\n- **Eligibility Criteria:** Universities usually set specific conditions for awarding grace marks, such as:\n  - **Number of Backlogs:** Some institutions allow grace marks only if you have a limited number of KTs.\n  - **Minimum Percentage:** You might need to maintain a certain overall percentage to qualify for grace.\n  - **Timely Application:** There might be deadlines by which you need to apply for grace marks.\n\n### **Steps You Should Take**\n1. **Review University Guidelines:**\n   - **Academic Regulations:** Check the latest academic regulations or handbook provided by MU (ensure you have the correct university name and access its resources).\n   - **Official Notifications:** Look for any official announcements regarding grace marks for your current academic year.\n\n2. **Contact Academic Office:**\n   - **Examination Department:** Reach out to the examination or academic affairs department for precise information.\n   - **Advisors or Faculty:** Speak with your academic advisor or faculty members who can provide guidance based on your academic standing.\n\n3. **Prepare Necessary Documentation:**\n   - **Academic Records:** Have your transcripts and any related documents ready when making inquiries.\n   - **Application Forms:** If required, fill out any forms for applying for grace marks within stipulated deadlines.\n\n4. **Consider Supplementary Exams:**\n   - **Clearing KT:** If grace marks aren't an option, plan to appear for your supplementary exam to clear the KT and improve your overall standing.\n\n### **Final Thoughts**\nPolicies can vary significantly between institutions, and even between different departments within the same university. Therefore, obtaining accurate and specific information from MU's official channels is crucial. Taking proactive steps by reaching out to the appropriate offices will provide clarity and help you navigate your academic path smoothly.\n\nGood luck with your studies, and I hope you successfully resolve your KT situation!",
